14 WHEREAS, the women of the Six Triple Eight worked around the clock to sort and deliver
15 packages and letters to soldiers, creating and maintaining their own card index system in
16 order to properly identify the large quantities of mail; and
17 WHEREAS, despite the sexual and racial discrimination they faced, the soldiers were able
18 to efficiently and effectively clear backlogs in the United Kingdom and France, processing
19 an estimated 65,000 pieces of mail per shift; and
20 WHEREAS, at the end of the war, the women of the 6888th received no public recognition
21 for their monumental contributions upon disbandment; and
22 WHEREAS, in December 2024, Tyler Perry wrote, directed, and produced a Netflix film
23 titled The Six Triple Eight, bringing light to the often under-represented stories of the
24 battalion; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the legacy of this exemplary battalion
26 and the women who served as part of it be appropriately honored.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
28 honor the resilience, efficiency, and determination of the women of the 6888th Central Postal
29 Directory Battalion and extend the most sincere gratitude for their distinguished service.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
32 press.
